Elements of felony murder include: 
- The killing of a human being; 
- The killing is committed during the commission of a felony; 
- The felony does not have to be directly related to the murder; 
- There is no requirement that the underlying felony results in death; 
- The perpetrator does not have to be involved in the underlying felony. 

Felony murder is different from other types of murder in that it does not require intent to kill. Furthermore, the perpetrator can be held liable for the death of an individual even if they did not actually kill the victim.
